<div class="inner-page">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="sci-hero">
    <div class="sci-hero-inner">
      <div class="section-eyebrow" style="color:#52B788;">Evidence-Based</div>
      <h1 class="sci-hero-title">The Science Behind Happie</h1>
      <p class="sci-hero-sub">We didn't invent functional mushrooms. We just made them delicious — and backed by the same research that's been building for decades.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Stats bar -->
  <div class="sci-stats">
    <div class="sci-stats-grid">
      <div class="sci-stat">
        <div class="sci-stat-num">2,000<span class="sci-stat-unit">mg</span></div>
        <div class="sci-stat-label">Per can total</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sci-stat">
        <div class="sci-stat-num">100%</div>
        <div class="sci-stat-label">Fruiting body</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sci-stat">
        <div class="sci-stat-num">3rd</div>
        <div class="sci-stat-label">Party tested every batch</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sci-stat">
        <div class="sci-stat-num">0</div>
        <div class="sci-stat-label">Artificial ingredients</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Why mushrooms work -->
  <section class="sci-section" style="background:var(--cream);">
    <div class="sci-inner">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">The Basics</div>
      <h2 class="sci-section-title">Why functional mushrooms work</h2>
      <div class="sci-two-col">
        <div class="sci-text-col">
          <p>Functional mushrooms aren't psychedelic. They're adaptogenic — meaning they help your body respond to stress, maintain homeostasis, and function optimally. They've been used in Asian medicine for thousands of years, and modern clinical research is validating what practitioners knew empirically.</p>
          <p>The key active compounds — <strong>beta-glucans</strong> (polysaccharides) and <strong>triterpenes</strong> — interact with your immune system, nervous system, and mitochondria in ways that are well-documented in peer-reviewed literature.</p>
          <p>The challenge has always been delivery and dosing. Most supplements bury them in capsules at sub-effective doses. We put effective doses in a drink that actually tastes good — so you actually take it daily.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sci-cards-col">
          <div class="sci-compound-card">
            <strong>Beta-Glucans</strong>
            <p>Water-soluble polysaccharides that modulate immune function and support neural health. Only captured through hot water extraction.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="sci-compound-card">
            <strong>Triterpenes</strong>
            <p>Fat-soluble compounds (especially in Reishi) responsible for adaptogenic and anti-inflammatory effects. Require alcohol extraction to release.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="sci-compound-card">
            <strong>Cordycepin</strong>
            <p>The primary active in Cordyceps — an adenosine analog that supports cellular energy production (ATP) without stimulating the adrenal system.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Dual extraction -->
  <section class="sci-section" style="background:#fff;">
    <div class="sci-inner">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Our Standard</div>
      <h2 class="sci-section-title">Dual extraction — the only way to get the full spectrum</h2>
      <div class="sci-extract-grid">
        <div class="sci-extract-card sci-extract-light">
          <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--green)" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3C12 3 5 10.5 5 15a7 7 0 0 0 14 0c0-4.5-7-12-7-12z"/><path d="M9.5 16.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 0 3.5 2"/></svg>
          <h3>Hot Water Extraction</h3>
          <p>Breaks down the chitin cell wall and releases water-soluble beta-glucans — the primary immune-modulating and nootropic compounds. This is what most mushroom teas do. It's necessary, but not sufficient.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sci-extract-card sci-extract-dark">
          <svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="rgba(255,255,255,0.85)" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M9 3h6l1 5H8L9 3z"/><path d="M8 8v10a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h6a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V8"/><path d="M12 12v3M11 14h2"/></svg>
          <h3>Alcohol Extraction</h3>
          <p>Releases fat-soluble triterpenes, sterols, and other non-polar compounds that hot water alone can't extract. Critical for Reishi's adaptogenic and anti-inflammatory properties. The step most brands skip.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sci-extract-note">
        <strong>The result: a full-spectrum extract</strong> — both the water-soluble and fat-soluble compounds working together, the way nature intended.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Fruiting body vs mycelium -->
  <section class="sci-section" style="background:var(--cream);">
    <div class="sci-inner" style="max-width:900px;">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Industry Transparency</div>
      <h2 class="sci-section-title">Fruiting body vs. mycelium — why it matters</h2>
      <div style="overflow-x:auto;-webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch;">
        <table class="sci-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th class="sci-th-feature">Feature</th>
              <th class="sci-th-happie">Fruiting Body (Happie ✅)</th>
              <th class="sci-th-other">Mycelium on Grain ❌</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="sci-td-feature">Beta-glucan content</td>
              <td class="sci-td-yes">High (30–40%)</td>
              <td class="sci-td-no">Low (5–10%)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="sci-tr-alt">
              <td class="sci-td-feature">Starch / grain content</td>
              <td class="sci-td-yes">None</td>
              <td class="sci-td-no">Up to 60%</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="sci-td-feature">Active compound density</td>
              <td class="sci-td-yes">Concentrated</td>
              <td class="sci-td-no">Diluted</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="sci-tr-alt">
              <td class="sci-td-feature">Cost to produce</td>
              <td class="sci-td-yes">Higher (worth it)</td>
              <td class="sci-td-no">Cheaper (explains usage)</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="sci-cta">
    <h2 class="sci-cta-title">Science you can taste.</h2>
    <p class="sci-cta-sub">2,000mg of dual-extracted, fruiting body mushrooms. In a can that actually tastes good.</p>
    <a href="/collections/all" class="btn-primary">Shop Now →</a>
  </section>

</div>

